UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
No. 6617
ORDER WITHDRAWING EXHIBITS
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF JUNICHI YAMAMOTO FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
Upon the application of the United States Attorney, and it appearing to the court that the above entitled cause has been concluded, and that the exhibits introduced by the Govern- ment, consisting of certain records of the Immigration Department, which were filed with the return herein, have served their purpose; it is hereby
ORDERED that the said exhibits may be withdrawn from the custody of the clerk of the court and delivered to the United States Attorney.
DONE in open court this 10 day of April 1922.
Neterer Judge
RECEIVED the above exhibits April 11 1922. THOS.P.REVELLE, United States Attorney, by C. L. Keen Clerk.
No. 6617
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF JUNICHI YAMAMOTO FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
ORDER WITHDRAWING EXHIBITS
GoB #9-Page 228
FILED IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT Western District of Washington NORTHERN DIVISION
Tx
APR 10 1922
F. M. Harshberger, Clerk By S.E. Leitch Deputy
